<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14415">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b>Check out the Digital Resource Guide for the Citizenship in
      the Community merit badge
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/digital-resource-guides/citizenship-community/"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      for detailed information and helpful resources to engage your learning and
      assist you along on your merit badge journey!<br />
      The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Citizenship%20in%20the%20Community.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14430">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor what citizenship in the community means and
      what it takes to be a good citizen in your community. Discuss the rights,
      duties, and obligations of citizenship, and explain how you can
      demonstrate good citizenship in your community, Scouting unit, place of
      worship, or school. <br /><i>Resources:</i
      ><a href="https://youtu.be/FWwEMFSY1r0" target="_blank"
        >Rights and Responsibilities (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Bv2XHEcGSOU" target="_blank"
        >Responsibilities of the Charter Commission (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14416">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14416 mb-requirement-id-14417">
        (a) Using an electronic mapping tool or paper map, locate and pinpoint
        the following services and landmarks in your community. Determine and
        record the distances from your home including driving time AND either
        walking or biking time. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://apps.nationalmap.gov/viewer/" target="_blank"
          >National Map (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.google.com/maps" target="_blank"
          >Google Maps (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://maps.apple.com/search" target="_blank"
          >Apple Map (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LBcZg9gRmbI" target="_blank"
          >How To Create a Table in a Word Document Online (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14417 mb-requirement-id-14434">
        (1) Chief government buildings such as your city hall, county
        courthouse, and public works/services facilities
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14417 mb-requirement-id-14435">
        (2) Fire station, police station, and hospital nearest your home
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14417 mb-requirement-id-14436">
        (3) Parks, playgrounds, recreation areas, and trails
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14417 mb-requirement-id-14437">
        (4) Historical or other interesting points of interest
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14416 mb-requirement-id-14418">
        (b) Chart the organization of your local or state government. Show the
        top offices and tell whether they are elected or appointed. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_sQNz2liUuY" target="_blank"
          >Three Branches of Government at the State Level (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gs6lqZEe4Rk" target="_blank"
          >The Role and Functions of Local Government (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14419">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14419 mb-requirement-id-14420">
        (a) Attend an in-person meeting of your city, town, or county council or
        school board, local court session; OR another state or local
        governmental meeting approved in advance by your counselor. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/E9ylFthKSkY" target="_blank"
          >How Does the US Court System Work? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fV1x0l3CAo0" target="_blank"
          >What Do School Boards Do? (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/uvJtYaaMH-k" target="_blank"
          >What Does My Local School Board Do? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-FK9THDgIT4" target="_blank"
          >How a City Council Meeting Works (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/J9G00lK-fsw" target="_blank"
          >Community Court (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14419 mb-requirement-id-14421">
        (b) Choose one of the issues discussed at the meeting where a difference
        of opinions was expressed, and explain to your counselor why you agree
        with one opinion more than you do another one. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://sulky-answer-76a.notion.site/Note-taking-assignment-tips-52758bb0f5a3486181c4b60b813e0338"
          target="_blank"
          >Note Taking Assignment Tips (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/uy6Eu5l0yOk" target="_blank"
          >Note Taking Methods (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14422">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Choose an issue that is important to the citizens of your community; then
      do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14422 mb-requirement-id-14423">
        (a) Find out which branch of local government is responsible for this
        issue.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14422 mb-requirement-id-14424">
        (b) With your counselor's and a parent or guardian's approval, interview
        one person from the branch of government you identified in requirement
        4(a). Ask what is being done about this issue and how young people can
        help. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6NG-XCwuWfk" target="_blank"
          >Tips and Tricks on Preparing and Conducting an Interview (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14422 mb-requirement-id-14425">
        (c) Share what you have learned with your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14431">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      With the approval of your counselor and a parent or guardian, watch a
      movie that shows how the actions of one individual or group of individuals
      can have a positive effect on a community. Discuss with your counselor
      what you learned from the movie about what it means to be a valuable and
      concerned member of the community. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/iMrdUCJuvlQ" target="_blank"
        >Remember the Titans Trailer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14432">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      List some of the services (such as the library, recreation center, public
      transportation, and public safety) your community provides that are funded
      by taxpayers. Tell your counselor why these services are important to your
      community. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/HJV7SbkeC60" target="_blank"
        >Taxes: What Do They Pay For (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.usaspending.gov/state" target="_blank"
        >Check Out Your State's Funding Today! (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14426">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14426 mb-requirement-id-14427">
        (a) Identify three charitable organizations outside of Scouting that
        interest you and bring people in your community together to work for the
        good of your community. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cdh2z3LHdTQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Find the Best Charities (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.charitynavigator.org/" target="_blank"
          >Charity Navigator (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.guidestar.org" target="_blank"
          >The Tax Exempt Organization Search Tool (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.bbb.org" target="_blank"
          >Better Business Bureau (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.redcross.org/red-cross-youth.html" target="_blank"
          >American Red Cross (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.habitat.org/volunteer/near-you/youth-programs"
          target="_blank"
          >Habitat for Humanity (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.ymca.org/get-involved/volunteer" target="_blank"
          >The YMCA (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14426 mb-requirement-id-14428">
        (b) Pick ONE of the organizations you chose for requirement 7(a). Using
        a variety of resources (including newspapers, fliers and other
        literature, the internet, volunteers, and employees of the
        organization), find out more about this organization. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ELT85QKsGDo" target="_blank"
          >Finding a Good Charity (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.idealist.org/en/volunteer" target="_blank"
          >Volunteer Opportunities (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.charitynavigator.org/" target="_blank"
          >Charity Navigator (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.charitywatch.org" target="_blank"
          >Charity Ratings (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://vimeo.com/1147095870?fl=ip&amp;fe=ec" target="_blank"
          >Mobile Food Pantry Eagle Project (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14426 mb-requirement-id-14429">
        (c) With your counselor's and your parent or guardian's approval,
        contact the organization you chose for requirement 7(b), and find out
        what young people can do to help. While working on this merit badge,
        volunteer at least eight hours of your time for the organization. After
        your volunteer experience is over, discuss what you have learned with
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mzV6yRHqGjQ" target="_blank"
          >Benefits of Community Service (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14433">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Develop a public presentation (such as a video, slide show, speech,
      digital presentation, or photo exhibit) about important and unique aspects
      of your community. Include information about the history, cultures, and
      ethnic groups of your community; its best features and popular places
      where people gather; and the challenges it faces. Stage your presentation
      in front of your counselor or a group, such as your patrol or a class at
      school. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/1sOgYNgq88E" target="_blank"
        >How To Organize and Deliver a Great Presentation (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
